The paper deals with the fundamental task of consensus in distributed computing, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of a Multiple Access Channel (MAC) prone to faults and a weak communication model called the "beeping model" suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The analysis of error probabilities and the design of a deterministic algorithm for global clock synchronization suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
